[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering the library issue**\n\nI'm thinking about how this library acts as a driver and whether AI could generate tests without Docker. There's a failure in the Java run due to an assertion error about a changes in the name format. The question suggests potential issues with library setup that go beyond normal test scaffolding.\n\nI wonder if they expect Docker for DB drivers, but according to Neo4j documentation, the normal approach connects directly to a server like localhost:7687. If there's no Docker image, tests would only cover local value mapping. I should also wrap my head around the Forge workflow for dependency management.\n\n**Deciding on library setup**\n\nI need to determine if the library requires setup that goes beyond the usual test scaffolding to achieve meaningful coverage. If I opt for using advisory preparation with Docker, should I go for the neo4j:5.28.8 tag? I wonder about the official Neo4j database image and its version compatibility with the Java driver. Does version 5.28.8 match the DBMS 5.28? I should also check the availability of other tags, like neo4j:5.28.1, as the compatibility details are mentioned in the driver README.\n\n**Inspecting neo4j version**\n\nI need to check the version of the neo4j image in the pom file. It seems like an important detail that might affect how everything runs. I'll make sure to look closely at that to ensure compatibility with the project's requirements. It's crucial to have the right version, so I'll take my time examining it before proceeding, as I want to avoid any issues that could come from using the wrong version. Let's see what I find!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0a7783f7e53607dd016a42554b8bd08193845857a916d3191a\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQlVYJtH7lMfxEjZWRZoK7o5PvRsZZ00ht_UQhBw_ENwWR9EZPaZhGZ83uHVkFWaHmJ-hROKOy8TrFiEENMPwM1pa1pgoWlE